      "node_type": "viral_pattern",
      "pattern_name": "Controversial Statement",
      "description": "The post starts with a controversial statement, challenging readers' assumptions about what is truly important in entrepreneurship. This immediately grabs attention and encourages engagement.",
      "bracket": "strong",
      "effectiveness": "high",
      "id": "pattern_4afacc87"
    },
    {
      "node_type": "viral_pattern",
      "pattern_name": "Personal Story",
      "description": "Both posts include personal stories or experiences that resonate with the audience. The author's situation and his response to it create a relatable scenario.",
      "bracket": "mega_viral",
      "effectiveness": "medium",
      "id": "pattern_a18fe02a"
    },
    {
      "node_type": "viral_pattern",
      "pattern_name": "Future Scenario",
      "description": "The second post presents a future scenario of AI-powered healthcare kiosks, which is intriguing and thought-provoking for the audience.",
      "bracket": "mega_viral",
      "effectiveness": "high",
      "id": "pattern_22fe1f6c"
    },
    {
      "node_type": "viral_pattern",
      "pattern_name": "Authority Figure",
      "description": "The third post mentions an authority figure (Karpathy) who has built something impressive ($50M executive team for $0.02 per decision), which adds credibility and intrigue to the content.",
      "bracket": "mega_viral",
      "effectiveness": "medium",
      "id": "pattern_c65a043f"
    },
    {
      "node_type": "viral_pattern",
      "pattern_name": "Engagement Trigger",
      "description": "The post ends with an open-ended question or challenge ('Identify recurring PATTERNS that make these posts viral'), inviting the audience to engage in discussion or reflection.",
      "bracket": "mega_viral",
      "effectiveness": "medium",
      "id": "pattern_d405f0f8"
    },
    {
      "node_type": "viral_pattern",
      "pattern_name": "Contrasting popular opinion",
      "description": "The author contrasts the over-sold concept of entrepreneurship with under-sold self-awareness and happiness. This creates a contrast that challenges common beliefs, making the post more engaging.",
      "bracket": "mega_viral",
      "effectiveness": "high",
      "id": "pattern_e33ef98a"
    },
    {
      "node_type": "viral_pattern",
      "pattern_name": "Vulnerability",
      "description": "The post reveals vulnerabilities in current strategies, such as the chip containment strategy not working or most Chinese companies accepting worse performance when switching from NVIDIA. This makes readers feel empathy and encourages them to take action.",
      "bracket": "strong",
      "effectiveness": "medium",
      "id": "pattern_ca548e0e"
    },
    {
      "node_type": "viral_pattern",
      "pattern_name": "Authority",
      "description": "The post is written by someone who invests in AI with data moats. Their expertise lends authority to their statements, making them more persuasive and credible.",
      "bracket": "strong",
      "effectiveness": "high",
      "id": "pattern_60f1a22c"
    },
    {
      "node_type": "viral_pattern",
      "pattern_name": "Future predictions",
      "description": "The author makes bold claims about future trends in the tech industry, such as identifying the next $1 trillion company and its potential business model. This creates anticipation and intrigue, driving engagement.",
